title: Up to 400,000 people remain along Gaza front after Israel rejects ‘pause’
description: A U.S. envoy estimated 350,000 to 400,000 people remain in northern Gaza as Israeli forces advance. In Jordan, Arab diplomats stepped up calls for a cease-fire.

title: Acapulco can rebuild from Hurricane Otis. But what about violent crime?
description: The Category 5 storm was only the latest calamity to hit the once-famed resort, pummeled by the pandemic and reeling from violent organized crime.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Blinken visits Jordan for talks; Netanyahu appears to reject humanitarian pauses
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken is due to meet Jordanian leaders in Amman, after a visit to Tel Aviv where he called for “humanitarian pauses.”

title: Earthquake in Nepal kills at least 132, destroys hundreds of homes
description: The 5.6-magnitude quake struck late Friday night. Rescue efforts were hobbled by poor roads in the mountainous area. Tremors were felt as far away as New Delhi.

title: Democratic House member accuses Biden of supporting Palestinian ‘genocide’
description: Rep. Rashida Tlaib (D-Mich.), the only Palestinian American in the House, posted a video to social media Friday seemingly to pressure Biden to support a cease-fire in the conflict.
